`template/` is the scaffold a project generator stamps out: Claude Code tool-hook wiring, git merge-driver config for context files, a CI workflow, and offline gate scripts, all bundled so a new project gets working context-maintenance and CI-gating from day one.

The pieces share one dependency chain: `.claude/settings.json` invokes `ctx-context`, `.gitattributes` invokes `ctx-regenerate` (unimplemented), and `scripts/` provides the CI-side checks that `ctx-verify` parses via a shared `FAIL:` convention — all three assume binaries/tools that `scripts/install-tools.sh` is responsible for fetching from a sibling tooling repo. If that bootstrap script's output paths or binary names change, both the Claude hook path and the git merge driver need updating in lockstep.

`.github/ci.yml` is the entry point that actually runs `scripts/*.sh` in CI; a new check script added under `scripts/` only takes effect once `.github/workflows/ci.yml` is updated to call it.

No intent.md exists at this level, so no divergence check applies.